<section class="not-prose mb-10 px-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mt-10">Implementation of User Feedback</h2>
  <p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
    After reviewing user responses from our <strong>Premier League Stats & Betting Website Feedback</strong> form, 
    we implemented several key design and functionality improvements. Below are the summarized findings and 
    how each was addressed in subsequent development sprints.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">1. Visual Appeal & UI Improvements</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
    <li>Average rating for visual appeal was <strong>3.5/5</strong>. Users described the UI as “too simple” and “basic.”</li>
    <li>We updated the <strong>homepage layout</strong> with improved spacing, typography, and team card design to make 
    the interface more modern and engaging.</li>
    <li>A new <strong>background image</strong> featuring a Premier League stadium replaced the plain background, aligning better 
    with the football theme while maintaining the recognizable league colors users liked.</li>
  </ul>

  
  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8">2. Navigation and Accessibility</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
    <li>Users indicated confusion about how to access past match statistics.</li>
    <li>We added <strong>clearer navigation hints and tooltips</strong> guiding users to click on past matches to view stats.</li>
    <li>Menu bar items were restructured under labeled categories (“Stats”, “Matches”, “Betting”) for easier access.</li>
  </ul>



  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8">3. Readability Enhancements</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
    <li>Users rated text readability very high (<strong>average 4.75/5</strong>), confirming color contrast and font sizing were effective.</li>
    <li>Minor improvements were made to font weight for stat labels and betting odds for better visibility on dark backgrounds.</li>
  </ul>


  
